<div id="review_1470435626" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1470435626" />
    <a title="Jeanette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11869072-jeanette"><img alt="Jeanette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1372095557p2/11869072.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1470435626?book_show_action=true">Dec 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeanette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeanette" href="/user/show/11869072-jeanette">Jeanette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1470435626" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13171989665584556278">This I enjoyed and rounded up from 3.5 star. Allende is an excellent story teller. Her copy is smooth and her characters tend to the dynamic. Here they certainly did. And each culture was reflected well to the relative sensibilities of their own dissimilar recognitions. That I love and it held 5 star for that quality in this novel. What a turbulent and exploding era!<br/><br/>Because of that individuality I did not deduct and forgave some strong examples of revisionist interpretation of the history.<br/><br/>So man</span>
  <span id="freeText13171989665584556278" style="display:none">This I enjoyed and rounded up from 3.5 star. Allende is an excellent story teller. Her copy is smooth and her characters tend to the dynamic. Here they certainly did. And each culture was reflected well to the relative sensibilities of their own dissimilar recognitions. That I love and it held 5 star for that quality in this novel. What a turbulent and exploding era!<br /><br />Because of that individuality I did not deduct and forgave some strong examples of revisionist interpretation of the history.<br /><br />So many others seem to protest the quick ending; I didn't read reviews and still heard this several times. Well, I thought the ending was perfect. As in life, the quest or identity of a decade can quickly turn around with age progression or a renewed interest ignited at an individual's core. Maturity does happen too. Not always within intelligent logic and such superior purpose though. Yet, some never do grow up and it still remains all about impulsive feelings. Thankfully it's probably most humans who can reason over emotive histrionics and "likeability" as they age and direct their purpose. Eliza did.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13171989665584556278" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

